## Key Changes from Previous FAS Version

The key updates include:

*   **Revision Note:** Addition of a note to indicate the revision date (01 July 2024 / 24 Muharram 1446) and the presence of updated clauses in a supplement specifically for Diminishing Musharaka arrangements in real estate funds.
*   **Enhanced Disclosure:** Expanded disclosure requirements to incorporate details about valuation methodology, appraiser qualifications, profit/loss distribution ratios according to the Shirkah al-ʿAqd agreement, and accounting for periodic ownership transfers in Diminishing Musharaka transactions in real estate funds.

{
  "pages": [
    {
      "title": "Title & Effective Date",
      "content": {
        "standard_number": "FAS 4 (Revised 2024)",
        "title": "Accounting for Diminishing Musharaka in Real Estate Funds",
        "example_title": "Accounting for Innovative Digital Assets",
        "effective_date": "01 July 2024 (Gregorian) / 24 Muharram 1446 (Hijri)",
        "issued_by": "AI-Driven Standard Enhancement System (Conceptual)"
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Objective, Scope & Key Principles",
      "content": {
        "objective": [
          "To provide specific guidance on the accounting treatment of Diminishing Musharaka arrangements within real estate funds.",
          "The standard clarifies valuation methodologies, disclosure requirements, and the application of Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd principles."
        ],
        "scope": {
          "applicable_transactions_entities": "This standard applies to Islamic Financial Institutions (IFIs) engaged in Diminishing Musharaka transactions for real estate investments. It specifically addresses the accounting for partner contributions, periodic ownership transfers, and partner exits.",
          "exclusions": "This standard does not cover Diminishing Musharaka arrangements outside the scope of real estate funds or those not structured as Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd partnerships."
        },
        "key_shariah_principles": [
          "Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd: The underlying partnership contract must adhere to Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd principles regarding capital contributions, profit and loss sharing, and management.",
          "Prohibition of Riba (Interest): All transactions must be free from any element of interest.",
          "Prohibition of Gharar (Uncertainty): The terms of the Diminishing Musharaka agreement must be clear and transparent, avoiding excessive uncertainty."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Definitions",
      "content": {
        "definitions": [
          {
            "term": "Diminishing Musharaka",
            "definition": "A form of Islamic financing where an IFI and a client jointly own an asset, with the IFI's ownership gradually transferred to the client over time through periodic payments."
          },
          {
            "term": "Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd",
            "definition": "A partnership contract in Islamic finance, defining the rights and obligations of each partner, including capital contributions, profit/loss sharing ratios, and management responsibilities."
          },
          {
            "term": "Fair Value",
            "definition": "The price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date."
          },
          {
            "term": "Independent Appraiser",
            "definition": "A qualified professional, independent of the IFI and the client, who possesses the necessary expertise and experience to determine the fair value of real estate assets."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Recognition and Initial Measurement",
      "content": {
        "recognition": {
          "general_criteria": "A Diminishing Musharaka investment in real estate shall be recognized when the IFI has rights and obligations arising from the Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd agreement and control over its share of the underlying asset.",
          "specific_points": "Initial capital contributions from each partner (IFI and client) shall be recognized at fair value at the inception of the Diminishing Musharaka agreement."
        },
        "initial_measurement": {
          "general_principle": "Upon initial recognition, the Diminishing Musharaka investment shall be measured at fair value.",
          "specific_guidance": "For in-kind contributions, the fair value shall be determined using appropriate valuation techniques, and the valuation method used must be disclosed."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Subsequent Measurement & De-recognition",
      "content": {
        "subsequent_measurement": {
          "measurement_basis": "For Diminishing Musharaka investments in real estate, the fair value of the underlying real estate asset shall be determined at least annually by an independent and qualified appraiser.",
          "changes_in_value": "Changes in fair value shall be recognized in equity based on the respective ownership percentages of the IFI and the client at the time of valuation.",
          "profit_loss_recognition": "The Diminishing Musharaka agreement shall explicitly state the agreed-upon ratios for profit and loss distribution, adhering to the principles of Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd. These ratios must be determined at the inception of the contract and remain fixed throughout the agreement's duration, unless mutually agreed otherwise according to Shariah principles."
        },
        "de_recognition": {
          "criteria": "The periodic transfer of ownership from the IFI to the client results in de-recognition of a portion of the IFI's investment.",
          "accounting": "The periodic transfer of ownership from the IFI to the client shall be accounted for as a reduction in the IFI's investment and a corresponding increase in the client's equity, reflecting the transfer of ownership at the agreed-upon price."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Disclosure Requirements",
      "content": {
        "qualitative_disclosures": [
          "Description of the nature of Diminishing Musharaka activities in real estate funds.",
          "Key accounting policies adopted for Diminishing Musharaka investments, including valuation methodologies.",
          "Information about risk management practices related to real estate investments and Shari'ah compliance.",
          "Explanation of how Shari'ah principles are adhered to in the structure and operation of the Diminishing Musharaka agreement."
        ],
        "quantitative_disclosures": [
          "Breakdown of carrying amounts of Diminishing Musharaka investments in real estate.",
          "Reconciliation of movements in carrying amounts, showing the impact of fair value changes and ownership transfers.",
          "Income/expense recognized from Diminishing Musharaka investments, including rental income and profit distributions.",
          "Maturity analysis of the Diminishing Musharaka agreements.",
          "Information on any impaired real estate assets and related provisions."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "Basis for Conclusions (Summary)",
      "content": {
        "rationale": "This standard addresses the lack of specific guidance in FAS 4 regarding the accounting treatment of Diminishing Musharaka arrangements in real estate funds. It focuses on valuation, disclosure, and adherence to Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd principles.",
        "shariah_compliance": "The standard ensures alignment with Shari'ah principles by mandating the use of independent appraisals, requiring transparency in transfer pricing, and adhering to pre-agreed profit and loss distribution ratios within the Shirkah al-\u02bfAqd framework.",
        "addressing_gaps": "This standard specifically addresses user concerns related to partner contributions and exits by providing clear guidance on initial capital contributions, periodic ownership transfers, and the accounting for partner exits, enhancing transparency and reducing uncertainty."
      }
    }
  ]
}
